gnacourt, Somme, Hauts-de-France, Frankrijk","Vignacourt, Somme, Picardie, France":"Vignacourt, Somme, Picardie, Frankrijk","Vignacourt, 80650, Somme, Hauts-de-France, FRANCE":"Vignacourt, Somme, Picardie, Frankrijk","France":"Frankrijk"},"en":{"1136–1178":"1136–1178","1134–1186":"1134–1186","1142–1189":"1142–1189","1159–Female":"1159–Deceased","1160–Male":"1160–Deceased","1165–Male":"1165–Deceased","1172–1229":"1172–1229","1103–1163":"1103–1163","1118–1174":"1118–1174","1165":"1165","1142":"1142","1186":"1186","1163":"1163","1174":"1174","1172":"1172","1160":"1160","1118":"1118","1159":"1159","1136":"1136","1103":"1103","1178":"1178","1189":"1189","1134":"1134","about 1165":"about 1165","1229":"1229","Vignacourt, Somme, Hauts-de-France, France":"Vignacourt, Somme, Hauts-de-France, France","Vignacourt, Somme, Picardie, France":"Vignacourt, Somme, Picardie, France","Vignacourt, 80650, Somme, Hauts-de-France, FRANCE":"Vignacourt, Somme, Picardie, France","France":"France","nameMeanings":[{"name":"de","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Dilip, Anirban, Gopal, Alok, Anindya, Arunava, Asit, Asok, Dibyendu, Goutam, Indra, Indranil.","Indian: variant of   Dey  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Dey","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Ashit, Indu, Naina, Partha, Soumya, Ajit, Anjan, Anjana, Anup, Arjun, Arun, Ashim.","English, Scottish, and Welsh: variant of   Day  .","German: topographic name from a field name in North Rhine-Westphalia, denoting a sizeable piece of land, from Middle Low German <i>dē</i> ‘thigh’ (referring to the shape of the property)."]}]},{"name":"II","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Japanese: written 井伊 ‘well’ and ‘that’, the name one of Japan's great daimyō families, originally based in Tōtōmi (now part of Shizuoka prefecture), later in Kōzuke (now Gunma prefecture) and Ōmi (now Shiga prefecture). Other variants of the name substitute either character with similar sounding characters such as 飯 ‘cooked rice’, 居 ‘residence’, and so forth. It was formerly Romanized as <b>Iyi</b>. — Note: In the population figure published by the US Census Bureau, the Roman number <i>II</i> (meaning ‘the second’, i.e. ‘the younger’ of the two bearers of the name) is apparently also counted as a surname <i>Ii</i>.","History: Ii Naomasa (1561–1602) was awarded lands in Kōzuke and Ōmi for his service in the civil wars that won the shōgunate (military dictatorship) for Tokugawa Ieyasu. His family built the beautiful castle of Hikone, which still stands. His descendant Ii Naosuke (1815–1860) ruled Japan for two years as Tairō (Great Elder) and played a major part in signing treaties that opened Japan to foreign trade at the end of the Tokugawa Shōgunate. He was assassinated by adherents of the anti-foreign party."],"variants":[]},{"name":"Adrein","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["From Latin.  See  <b>Adrian</b>   ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Adrein de Wignacourt II was born in 1136, in Vignacourt, Somme, Hauts-de-France, France, his father, Adrein de Wignacourt, was 33 and his mother, Gersende de Montreuil, was 18. He had at least 2 sons and 2 daughters with Isabeau De Domart Dame de Saint-Leger. He died in 1178, at the age of 42."},"et":{"1136–1178":"1136–1178","1134–1186":"1134–1186","1142–1189":"1142–1189","1159–Female":"1159–Surnud","1160–Male":"1160–Surnud","1165–Male":"1165–Surnud","1172–1229":"1172–1229","1103–1163":"1103–1163","1118–1174":"1118–1174","1165":"1165","1142":"1142","1186":"1186","1163":"1163","1174":"1174","1172":"1172","1160":"1160","1118":"1118","1159":"1159","1136":"1136","1103":"1103","1178":"1178","1189":"1189","1134":"1134","about 1165":"umbes 1165","1229":"1229","Vignacourt, Somme, Hauts-de-France, France":"Vignacourt, Somme, 